wikipedia_page.main: Frederick Parker (18 June 1886 – 5 January 1963), also known as Spider Parker or Bassie Parker, was an English professional football forward and manager who played in the Football League for Clapton Orient. He was the first person to enlist in the Football Battalion during the First World War.

response: Frederick or Fred Parker may refer to:
